content:
Knab was founded in 2012 because we wanted to do things differently. Simpler, smarter, and more advantageous for our customers. Because we believe we can help everyone maximize their financial affairs. Our mission is to ensure that our clients "Feel at ease when it comes to their finances. Every day." By combining smart technical solutions with a healthy dose of human intelligence, we create financial services that really meet the needs of our clients. Add to that some of the sublime personal service from our employees and you end up with something that is truly unique to the world of finance.  

What will you do?
As a member of the Business Control team you act as a business partner for the value streams (business lines) by providing strategic advice and analysis supporting the value stream leads in optimizing business performance. 
Here's a snapshot of what an average day could look like; 
Starting the day with a catch-up with the head of Daily Use, finding out about the latest business developments and initiatives. Resulting in your involvement of a project to act as the financial conscious ensuring the financial viability of the initiative is sufficiently detailed and scrutinized. Next you meet with the project owner of a newly approved project to discuss the statement of work for an external service provider that will provide resources to manage the project. You have lunch with the team and after lunch you have an online meeting with the Group Finance manager of our shareholders, discussing the operating expense developments of the previous quarter. Finishing the day in the office with the Capital Management team to discuss and finalize the quarterly forecast for submission to the Executive Board. 
In your role you can quickly take responsibility, but you have the backing of a team seasoned as business controllers. The responsibility you will be able to take depends on your experience, given the size and growth of Knab there is always room to take on new and more responsibility. This provides you with the opportunity to be able to influence your own growth path and direction that fits your skills, capabilities, and ambitions. 

The team
Knab's Business Control team currently consists of 6 professionals. In this position, you will report to our Head of Business Control. 

Your profile
We expect you to be most successful in this position if you: 

have a master's degree in finance or a related field; 
3-5 years of experience in business or financial control or a closely related role. Banking experience is great but not a must-have; 
have the ambition to make an impact on the development of our business lines (value streams); 
have a well-developed analytical and problem-solving ability; 
are data-driven; 
are eager to learn and are result-oriented; 
are communicatively who is quality-oriented and tenacious. 


Diversity Statement: 
Come as you are. Knab is an open workplace with positive vibes. We are inclusive of all nationalities, races and genders. We feel comfortable to bring our authentic whole selves to work and like you to do so too. 

Work with us!
If you come to work with us, Knab will become a significant part of your life. Therefore, we make sure the ambiance is just as exciting as your job. 

We do not collaborate with 3rd parties to fulfil this role.
